    {
      "id": "pathshala_upanishads_chapter_1_1.2",
      "ref": "1.2",
      "chapter": 1,
      "sanskrit": "अन्यच्छ्रेयोऽन्यदुतैव प्रेयस्ते उभे नानार्थे पुरुषं सिनीतः । तयोः श्रेय आददानस्य साधु भवति हीयतेऽर्थाद्य उ प्रेयो वृणीते ॥",
      "transliteration": "anyachchreyo'nyadutaiva preyaste ubhe nānārthe puruṣaṁ sinītaḥ | tayoḥ śreya ādadānasya sādhu bhavati hīyate'rthādya u preyo vṛṇīte ||",
      "text": "The good (Shreya) and the pleasant (Preya) are different. Both of these bind a person. It goes well with him who clings to the good, but he who chooses the pleasant misses the true end of life.",
